Senior Consultant - Data Engineering

Are you a seasoned data engineering professional who excels in developing data-driven solutions? Do you have a passion for leading transformational initiatives that deliver measurable business success? If solving complex challenges and driving innovative outcomes excites you, Synogize wants to meet you!

We‚Äôre seeking a Senior Consultant with a deep understanding of Data Engineering to join our dynamic team in Melbourne. To be considered, candidates must have full, permanent working rights in Australia and at least 5+ years of industry experience in Data Engineering.

About You

You are someone who:

Collaborates closely with clients, designing tailored analytics strategies to solve complex business challenges.
Leads technical problem-solving efforts, optimizing data to deliver impactful insights.
Transforms business needs into actionable data models that drive strategic decision-making.

Key Responsibilities

Data Modeling & Architecture: Design, build, and maintain scalable data models that meet both client and internal needs.
ETL Development: Oversee the development of robust ETL/ELT pipelines, transforming raw data into structured, analyzable datasets.
Data Transformation: Lead SQL-based transformations using tools like dbt and Coalesce, delivering clean datasets for analysis.
Analytics Solutions: Integrate and manage analytics platforms (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, Looker) with data sources, working closely with BI and data teams.
Data Quality & Governance: Implement data governance frameworks to ensure data accuracy and integrity.
Client Leadership: Guide clients through technical challenges and deliver high-impact solutions that meet business goals.
Cross-functional Collaboration: Work with data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders to drive data-driven decision-making.
Performance Optimization: Monitor and improve the scalability and performance of data models and pipelines.

Required Skills & Experience

Advanced SQL expertise (5+ years) with strong experience in complex queries, stored procedures, and managing large datasets.
Hands-on experience with cloud platforms like Snowflake, BigQuery, Fabric, or Databricks.
Mastery of ETL/ELT processes and modern data transformation tools (e.g., dbt, Coalesce).
Expertise in creating compelling data visualizations using tools like Tableau, Power BI, or Looker.
Excellent communication skills, capable of explaining complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
Proven ability to deliver real-time analytics solutions in dynamic environments.

Bonus Skills

Machine learning or advanced data science techniques.
Passion for data storytelling and creating engaging visualizations.
Experience in data governance and ensuring data security, quality, and accuracy.

Required Qualifications

Must hold a valid permanent work visa, permanent residency, or Australian citizenship.
Bachelor's or Graduate's Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering, Applied math, Statistics, Physics, or equivalent experience.

We're looking for an experienced Data Migration Lead to join our team at our Sime Office in Melbourne Street, South Brisbane. This is a Permanent, Monday to Friday role.

As a Data Migration Lead at Sime Industrial, you will oversee data related activities including data migration readiness and execution, data modelling and cleansing, data environment setup, data security and compliance as part of our division wide ERP and Dealer Management System migration program.

You'll be responsible for:

Develop Data Migration Strategy: Plan and execute migration from legacy systems, ensuring data quality, governance, and compliance.
Lead Data Migration Activities: Oversee readiness and execution, including mapping, cleansing, transforming, and validating data.
Modernize Enterprise Infrastructure: Design data platform architecture and create transition roadmaps to support modernization.
Stakeholder Engagement: Build strong relationships, address concerns, and ensure alignment across projects.
Problem Solving & Innovation: Analyse complex issues, identify root causes, and propose creative solutions.
Drive Performance & Accountability: Motivate teams, hold self and others accountable, and deliver on commitments.
Contribute to Strategy: Operate effectively in ambiguous situations and adapt to change.

What you'll need:

Advanced in business requirements analysis and stakeholder engagement.
Strong planning and organizing skills for workflow optimization and resource management.
Expertise in architecture design and IT integration (Azure DevOps, CI/CD).
Advanced in data collection, analysis, and reporting.
Skilled in business process improvement and strategic direction.
Experience in enterprise readiness assessment and compliance.
Proficient in data control and migration (ETL, data pipeline design).
Master's degree (or equivalent) and substantial relevant experience.

Who are we and why work with us?

Sime is a partner of choice for some of the world's best brands in the Industrial and Motors sectors. With operations in 17 countries and territories and a strong footprint in Asia Pacific, we continue to grow, delivering sustainable value to our stakeholders through operational excellence, high-performance standards and good corporate governance.

When you join our team, you'll benefit from:

Flexibility & Work-Life Balance - We prioritize your well-being with flexible working hours

There to care. Here for good.

Aged care is so important. Some people forget that. You don't and neither do we. Because helping people is what we were born to do. We've been a leading provider of aged care in communities across South Australia since 1953. That's a long journey, and we're proud of our stability and strength.

Now, we're on a mission to continue to grow and improve our services and impact, hand in hand with our fantastic team. Here, every moment matters and every client counts. And so do you.

Join our team as a Senior People Systems Analyst (Oracle) and shape your future and ours.

A brighter future with Helping Hand, for older people and for you.

As our Senior People Systems Analyst (Oracle), you'll be at the heart of Helping Hand's digital transformation, ensuring we realise the full potential of our people systems, known as MyHR.

Following our system implementation, this role will be critical in taking us to the next level through optimising system functionality, effectiveness and user experience.

You'll be part of streamlining legacy paper-based processes, configuring and launching exciting new functionality (including the Oracle HCM Talent module), and strengthening system capability across the organisation.

Your work will enhance efficiency, free up our People team to focus on what matters most, our people and improve the employee experience across every stage of the journey. As our go-to Oracle HCM expert, you'll drive the next phase of our digital transformation:


Lead all Oracle HCM configuration and optimisation: activating the system strategy, new module rollouts (Talent, Learning, Recruitment), and continuous improvement across Core HR.
Build internal capability by mentoring and upskilling our People team to use the system effectively, reducing vendor dependency and building long-term resilience.
Own the technical relationship with Oracle and our vendors, managing roadmap enhancements, troubleshooting complex issues, and ensuring we're maximising our investment.
Develop dashboards and reports that give leaders real insight into our people and operations
Drive change and adoption initiatives that help our teams realise the full potential of MyHR

What you'll bring

To succeed in this role, you will have:


Extensive hands-on experience in the administration and configuration of HR platforms, including specifically Oracle HCM .
Proven experience implementing and enhancing HR systems and workflows.
Strong technical understanding of Core HR, Recruitment, Learning and Talent Oracle modules.
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills, you translate business needs into digital solutions in a way that brings stakeholders on the journey.
High levels of initiative, organisation, and creative problem-solving skills.

You'll stand out from the crowd if you have some of the following:


Experience in aged care, health or not-for-profit environments.
Familiarity with payroll or time and attendance systems.
Exposure to integrating Oracle and AI-enabled HR functionality.


Why Helping Hand?

We get it - a role in aged care is more than just money. You don't do it for the pat on the back. You do it because you know it matters - and at Helping Hand, you matter, too

We truly care about how you are. Here are some of the things we hope you'll love about working with us:

We are who you are

Here's the thing. When good people come together, amazing things happen. At Helping Hand, you'll find real support from teammates and managers who share your values and strength. They've been in your shoes - and they'll always be just a phone call away to lend a helping hand.

We are where you are

As our Senior People Systems Analyst (Oracle) you'll know you're contributing directly to a community you care about. And you'll see your impact on the faces of the people you're supporting.

We care how you are

In any job, how well you feel affects how well you work. And we take that very seriously. We want you to feel as secure as you can. So, we're proud that our people say they value the stability that comes with working for a well-established, growing organisation like us.

You'll also enjoy a range of other benefits:


Be part of a warm, friendly team that genuinely cares about you and your wellbeing
Maximise your take-home pay by salary packaging up to $15,899 each year
Enjoy an additional $2,650 tax free per year with our Meal and Entertainment Card
Prioritise your health and wellbeing with discounted private health insurance, plus our Employee Assistance Program

Are you ready to lend a Helping Hand?

Join us at Helping Hand and help shape your future and ours.
